The paper discusses the use of restricted Boltzmann machines (RBMs) and their extensions in machine learning, which falls under the category of neural networks and deep learning. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of simulations of digital memcomputing machines (DMMs) to accelerate the training of RBMs, which falls under the category of computational complexity and optimization, and could be classified under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
